Introduction to Ayurvedic Mental Wellness

{/* Ayurveda’s View on Mental Health */}

Ayurveda’s View on Mental Health (Manas Shastra)

  • Sattva (Balance, Purity, Clarity): Leads to peace, wisdom, and happiness.
  • Rajas (Activity, Passion, Agitation): Causes stress, ambition, and restlessness.
  • Tamas (Inertia, Darkness, Ignorance): Leads to laziness, confusion, and depression.
{/* Common Mental Health Issues & Solutions */}
{/* Stress & Anxiety */}

Stress & Anxiety (Chittodvega)

Caused by Vata Dosha imbalance.

  • Herbs: Ashwagandha, Brahmi, Jatamansi.
  • Breathing: Anulom Vilom, Bhramari Pranayama.
  • Lifestyle: Grounding foods, oil massages.
{/* Depression */}

Depression (Vishada Roga)

Caused by Tamas dominance.

  • Herbs: Shankhpushpi, Jatamansi, Tulsi.
  • Yoga: Sun Salutations, meditation.
  • Diet: Warm, nourishing foods.
{/* Insomnia */}

Insomnia (Anidra)

Caused by Vata-Pitta imbalance.

  • Herbs: Brahmi tea, Ashwagandha.
  • Routine: Early sleep, essential oils.
  • Diet: Avoid caffeine before bed.
{/* Ayurvedic Herbs & Remedies */}

Ayurvedic Herbs & Remedies for Mental Wellness

  • Ashwagandha: Reduces cortisol, enhances relaxation.
  • Brahmi: Improves focus, memory, and clarity.
  • Shankhpushpi: Calms the nervous system, reduces overthinking.
  • Jatamansi: A natural antidepressant for emotional stability.
{/* Yoga & Meditation Practices */}

Yoga & Meditation Practices

  • Pranayama: Anulom Vilom (Balances brain), Bhramari (Deep relaxation).
  • Yoga Asanas: Child’s Pose (Relieves anxiety), Shavasana (Induces relaxation).
  • Guided Meditation: Mantra Chanting (Om, So Hum), Mindful Eating & Walking.
